==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feudary
<hw>Feu"da*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>feudarius</ets>, fr. <ets>feudum</ets>. See 2d
<er>Feud</er>.]</ety> <def>Held by, or pertaining to, feudal
tenure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feudary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Feudary
<hw>Feu"da*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A tenant who holds
his lands by feudal service; a feudatory.</def>
<rj><au>Foxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A feodary. See <er>Feodary</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feudatary</ent>⟦br⟧
